on\" aria-controls=\"aria-mchl17cf0e7a\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">If your AirPods are connected with your iPhone</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl17cf0e7a\"><p>If you already connected your AirPods with your iPhone, they’re ready to use with your Mac (your Mac must support Handoff and you must be signed in to iCloud using the same Apple ID).</p><ul class=\"ListSingle\"><li><p> Open the AirPods case, click the Volume control <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/ea0b768246888e7447b8b510f264c789.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"28\" width=\"37\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_volume_osx.png\"> in the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=menu-bar&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL385F1EEA&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">menu bar</a> on your Mac, then choose AirPods.</p></li></ul></div></div><div id=\"mchl22476fc2\" class=\"Task\"><h2 role=\"button\" aria-controls=\"aria-mchl22476fc2\" aria-expanded=\"true\" class=\"Name\">Connect your AirPods with your Mac</h2><div class=\"TaskBody\" role=\"region\" aria-hidden=\"false\" id=\"aria-mchl22476fc2\"><p>If your AirPods are not connected with your iPhone, you can connect them directly with your Mac.</p><ol><li><p>With your AirPods in their case, open the lid.</p></li><li><p>Press and hold the setup button on the back of the case until the status light flashes white.</p></li><li><p>On your Mac, choose Apple menu <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/5BFDD3F8094622802EEE504F/5BFDD3F9094622802EEE5056/en_US/ea0b768246888e7447b8b510f264c789.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"28\" width=\"37\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_volume_osx.png\"> &gt; System Preferences, then click Bluetooth.</p><p><a href=\"x-help-action://openPrefPane?bundleId=com.apple.preferences.Bluetooth\" class=\"URL\">Open Bluetooth preferences for me</a></p></li><li><p>Select AirPods in the Devices list, then click Connect.</p></li></ol></div></div><p>To use Siri or handle phone calls, double-tap one of the AirPods (you only have to be wearing one). For more information, go to the <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/airpods\" class=\"URL\">AirPods Support website</a>.</p><div class=\"Alert\"><p class=\"Tip\"><strong class=\"tip\">Tip: </strong>If your AirPods support it, say “Hey Siri.” If Siri doesn’t respond, open Siri preferences and make sure Listen for “Hey Siri” on AirPods is turned on. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=change-siri-preferences-on-mac&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL3FD7FC15&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Change Siri preferences</a>.</p></div><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-up-a-bluetooth-audio-device&amp;version=10.14&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH26833&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=10.14\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Set up a Bluetooth audio device to work with Mac</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["DisplayVersion/macOS Mojave 10.14","IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","ContentMode/liveContent","ArchivalStatus/Unarchived","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexON","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"3950"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"7864"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":